page.title: 06PARK WOODS
page.content: Park Woods is one of the largest woods in the borough,and has a wide variety of wildlife.Deer,foxes,rabbits and many species of birds are to be found along with bats.It is a deciduous wood with oak,birch and hornbeam being the most commonly found trees.The ground is covered with ferns,bracken and moss in which many small mammals,like mice,hedgehogs and voles live.Adders and grass-snakes are found throughout the wood and a large population of these and many kinds of amphibians like frogs and toads are resident in the nature reserve.This is an area of the wood,next to Haste Hill golf course which has been fenced off and allowed to grow naturally.
